-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - Dec 5
-- 
-- Fri Dec 05, 2014 03:08AM EST
-- None



SOFIA, Dec 5 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Friday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- The Court of Appeal in the southern city of Plovdiv upheld the ruling of the Pazardzhik District Court to keep under arrest seven Bulgarian nationals accused of preaching radical Islam as there was risk they might commit other crimes (Trud, Presa). -- The European Commission is unfreezing the EU funds under Operational Programme Regional Development, that were suspended for Bulgaria in the middle of the year, Vice President of the European Commission and Commissioner for Budget and Human Resources Kristalina Georgieva said (Standart, Presa). -- Following torrential rains, some parts of Bulgaria have been heavily flooded with several rivers and dams overflowing with the most affected districts being Vidin, Burgas, Yambol, Haskovo and Sliven (Trud, Presa). -- Petar Penchev has been named as Bulgarian first division club Botev Plovdiv coach on a temporary basis. He replaced Velislav Vutsov, who was sacked earlier this week (Meridian Match, Presa).